item.description:
We are thrilled to announce that the La Manno Lab has been awarded a European Research Council (ERC) Starting Grant for the project &ldquo;MOVIOLA: Cell decision capture and control via joint Raman live and omics profiling.&rdquo;
This 5-year grant (Feb 2026 - Jan 2031, 1.5 million euros) will support our research into understanding the molecular determinants that govern neural cell fate decisions during human brain development.
The MOVIOLA project introduces a novel experimental paradigm that combines live Raman microscopy with multi-modal molecular profiling to capture cells at the precise moments when fate decisions occur.
